race.comment: JASON DARREN (2) raced on speed and fought on bravely for second over this trip at Scone, backing up a previous placing. Consistent and finds the right race to break through. PRINCE OF PROPHETS (4) finished powerfully to score over 1300m at Narromine second-up. Improving type who looks a major threat to go back-to-back. DOWN THE KOOKA (16) improved last start, finishing a close fourth at Muswellbrook. Gets a key booking in Bullock from a favourable draw. Capable. THE DRAFTER (5) closed off well for third at Narromine over this trip. Gets in well again with the claim and is race fit. Can give this a shake. BLACKFISH (7) delivered a tough maiden win two starts ago and still has upside. Worth keeping safe.
